cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper presents a meta-learning method for learning parametric loss functions that can generalize across different tasks and model architectures. The paper discusses the application of this method in supervised and reinforcement learning tasks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of learned loss functions in computer vision tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV. Finally, the paper discusses the flexibility of the meta-learning framework to incorporate additional information, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.RO (robotics).
